      • logi

        public static void logi(String format,
                        Object... args)
        Print out log with System.out.println().
        Note: this method will print out caller if printCaller is true.
        Calling logi() etc. is recommended add a static final boolean flag before calling:
        if (staticBoolean) Util.logi("messages");
        In this way, the java compiler will optimize the code to nothing if the staticBoolean is false.
        Parameters:
        format -
        args -
